<section class="glossary" id="glossary">
    <h2>Glossary</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Exoplanet:</strong> A planet that orbits a star outside our solar system.</li>
        <li><strong>Habitable Zone:</strong> The region around a star where conditions might be right for liquid water.</li>
        <li><strong>Transit Method:</strong> A technique to detect exoplanets by measuring the dimming of a star.</li>
        <li><strong>Radial Velocity:</strong> A method that measures the star's wobble due to gravitational pull from a planet.</li>
        <li><strong>Neutron Star:</strong> A compact star formed after a supernova, with extreme density.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

