<section id="faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>How many exoplanets are there?</strong> There are over 5,000 confirmed exoplanets as of now.</li>
        <li><strong>Can exoplanets support life?</strong> Some exoplanets are located in the habitable zone, where conditions might support life.</li>
        <li><strong>What is the farthest exoplanet discovered?</strong> The farthest known exoplanet is approximately 13 billion light-years away.</li>
        <li><strong>Are exoplanets all gas giants?</strong> No, they can be rocky, gaseous, or icy.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

